    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-18T16:53:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-18T16:53:00-05:00" n="607"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d607">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">617.18/5–1754:Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Nicaragua</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d607fn1">This telegram, drafted and approved by Mr.
                            <persName corresp="#p_NJD1">Neal</persName>, was repeated for
                        information to San José as telegram 147.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-18T17:53:00-04:00"
                            >May 18, 1954—5:53 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>155. Department considers Nicaraguan-Costa Rican matter (<gloss
                        target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 159)<note n="2" xml:id="d607fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> unless dispassionately handled may
                    cause intensification difficulties these two countries which would distract our
                    mutual efforts rid Hemisphere especially Central American area of international
                    Communist threat. Inability two Governments settle this matter with as little
                    fanfare as possible would inevitably influence US public and official opinion
                    regarding rapid implementation grant military assistance program. Embassy San
                    Jose has been authorized approach <persName corresp="#p_FFJ1"
                        >Figueres</persName> counseling dispassionate diplomatic reply.</p>
                <p>Should opportunity present itself you are authorized inform <persName
                        corresp="#p_SGA1">Somoza</persName> above. In event opportunity not arise
                    and in your discretion you consider it advisable you are authorized approach
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGA1">Somoza</persName> with foregoing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
